# Git commits — no Cursor attribution

When creating git commits in this repository:

- **Never** use `git commit --trailer "Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>"` or any `--trailer` for Cursor.
- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `cursoragent`, or `cursoragent@cursor.com` to commit messages.
- Use plain commits only: `git commit -m "message"` (no co-author trailers).
- If the user asks to commit, write the message yourself and run a normal `git commit -m` without attribution trailers.

This keeps GitHub Contributors showing only the human author.
